# BACKLOG — mockspace-template

Future work tracked for mockspace-template. Each entry has a trigger condition and a sketch of the change. Items here are NOT in-flight; they wait for the trigger.

## Custom filters and functions

The minijinja-wrapped `TemplateEnv` exposes no custom filters in v1. As concrete needs emerge, register the following:

### `mockspace_field(name)` — typed lookup with informative error

Trigger: when a template references a field that consumers commonly typo (project_name vs project-name etc.).

Sketch: a function-style template helper that fetches a field by name and emits a render-time error with the available field list if the name is wrong. Stricter than minijinja's default error which just says "undefined".

### `repo_root` — platform-aware path resolution

Trigger: when templates need to emit absolute paths that must work across both per-repo (when mockspace bootstraps inside a consumer repo) and workspace-level (when homma runs across multiple repos) contexts.

Sketch: a function returning the appropriate `repo_root` for the current render call; the consumer registers the resolver at TemplateEnv construction.

### `format_byline()` — well-formed Co-Authored-By trailers

Trigger: when the workspace's byline policy (see `~/Dev/clause-dev/.claude/rules/ai-agent-framing.md`) needs templated emission. Deferred until commit-message templating becomes a thing.

Sketch: takes an agent identifier and emits `Co-Authored-By: <name> <email>` with correct formatting.

## Additional Platform impls

Built-in platforms in v1 are `ClaudePlatform` and `CopilotPlatform`. New platforms ship as new impls when their format stabilizes.

### CursorPlatform

Trigger: Cursor's rule-file format reaches stable conventions (paths under `.cursor/rules/`, frontmatter shape, hook surface).

Sketch: matches the Claude/Copilot pattern; lives in this crate behind a `cursor` cargo feature flag.

### CodeiumPlatform / AiderPlatform / other agent tools

Same shape as above; each lands when the target tool's format is stable enough to support.

## minijinja extension points

### Template include resolution

minijinja's `{% include %}` resolves through the `Environment`'s loader. Today consumers register templates by name explicitly. A filesystem-loader extension would let templates `{% include "shared/header.md.tmpl" %}` against a search path.

Trigger: when multiple templates need to share boilerplate (the workspace shared-fragment pattern would benefit).

Sketch: wrap minijinja's `Source` API; expose a `TemplateEnv::add_source_dir(path)` that registers a search path.

### Render-time data fetching (HTTP / file system)

Trigger: when workspace docs need to embed live data (current commit SHA, repo list from forge API, etc.).

Sketch: register custom functions that perform IO; gated behind a `live-data` cargo feature flag so the default render path stays pure.

## Live-port readiness criteria

Conditions for porting mock-crate code into mockspace root `src/`:

1. At least one external consumer (homma) has exercised the full API surface end-to-end.
2. Platform trait signature has not changed across two consumer cycles (i.e. one revision of the trait and one period of stable usage post-revision).
3. minijinja choice not displaced by a better template engine in the Rust ecosystem.
4. `IntoMockspaceConfig` trait usage validated by at least one non-mockspace-toml config schema (homma.toml is the canonical first one).

When these hold, a follow-up round ports the mock-crate `src/` into mockspace root, deletes the internal `src/render_*.rs` modules, and publishes mockspace-template to crates.io as a real consumer-facing crate.

## Substrate adoption (future)

When this crate ports into mockspace root and eventually consumes the workspace substrate:

- `String` → `hilavitkutin_str::Str` for non-static strings
- `PathBuf` → reconsider; might stay std `PathBuf` (filesystem ops boundary) or move to a workspace path primitive if one emerges
- `Option<T>` → `notko::Maybe<T>`
- `Result<T, E>` → `notko::Outcome<T, E>` (or `notko::Just<T>` for infallible hot paths)
- `Vec<T>` in public APIs → `impl IntoIterator<Item = T>` or `&[T]`
- Raw numeric primitives (none in current public surface, but watch for `usize` counts) → `arvo::USize` / `arvo::Cap<N>` / `arvo::UFixed<I, F, S>`

This adoption is deliberately deferred. The meta-tool layer doesn't need substrate types for v1; introducing them now would entangle mockspace's bootstrap with the substrate's evolution, which is exactly the entanglement the workspace structure avoids.

